,@DavidMeister I understand the original rationale and don't really have a whole lot of complaints with it. I am just explaining why I think it should be fixed now in newer version of languages, reflexive `==` is really nice to have, while it's true that floats break a lot of laws, most of them are only broken ""slightly"", and optimizations assuming they exist will almost never cause real problems, but this is totally different and plenty of optimizations are unsafe under `NaN != NaN`. such as shortcutting equality by comparing pointers first.","Embed Field: In MongoDB, using Java how can I query to find documents exceeding 15 MB storage size in a database or collection
